external_knowledge:
High-value cryptocurrencies refer to those with an average price greater than $1000; 
The specific user refers to the account with user_id 0 in the watchlist table; 
The last week refers to the 7-day period preceding the current date, as determined by the DATE('now', '-7 days') function in SQLite.

- 'treasure trove of cryptocurrencies' refers to the cryptocurrencies in the watchlist; 
- 'shone bright with an average price of over 2000 dollars' means the average price is greater than $2000; 
- 'sparkle' refers to the average price of the cryptocurrency; 
- 'trading chest' refers to the total trading volume of the cryptocurrency.
